    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a clear focal point in **Yordan Alvarez**, whose score of 87.42 represents our highest ceiling. Facing Young, **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from an elite park factor and favorable SP xERA, positioning him to anchor our production in R and RBI. Following closely is **Trea Turner**, our primary engine for SB scarcity. Despite a slight penalty for facing an elite defensive catcher, **Trea Turner** remains a mandatory start; his position at the top of the order combined with Houser\u2019s mediocre xERA suggests a high likelihood of reaching base and providing the stolen base upside we prioritize. **Kyle Schwarber** also draws a strong 70.37 rating against Houser, with his elite xwOBA effectively neutralizing any platoon disadvantage, making this a high-leverage pairing against the rotation.\n\nIn the middle of the lineup, **Colt Keith** and **Kazuma Okamoto** provide steady, high-floor output. **Colt Keith** benefits from a strong order placement and favorable platoon split, pushing his efficiency into the low 60s. **Carson Benge** represents our most marginal start at 56.03; he remains in the lineup due to the lack of available depth, but his placement at the bottom of the order and the presence of Mikolas on the mound warrant close monitoring. The most difficult personnel decision was benching **Jerar Encarnacion**, who fell just shy of our 40.0 floor at 39.39. While his platoon advantage is decent, the combination of a bottom-third lineup spot and a tough matchup against S\u00e1nchez keeps him on the bench to preserve our game caps.\n\nRisks today are moderate, with no major weather concerns, though the volatility of Houser\u2019s command remains a variable for both **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber**. We remain cognizant that with **Junior Caminero**, **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, and **Caleb Durbin** all sidelined by scheduled off-days, our bench depth is temporarily constrained. We will look to potential pinch-hit contributions or late-inning defensive substitutions from **Lars Nootbaar** or **Josh Smith** if the game scripts turn stagnant, but for now, the Zebras are committed to the projected efficiency of our core six starters.",
